rments with loose folds, flaps, or hanging sleeves, or who had fleshy folds of skin on his face, neck, or body.","German: nickname for a simple-minded person, from Middle Low German <i>lappe</i> ‘fool’. This surname (in any of the two possible senses; see also 1 above) is also found in France (mainly Alsace, also Lorraine).","English: nickname from Anglo-Norman French <i>lappe</i> ‘burdock’, perhaps for someone with a prickly character."]}]},{"name":"Ithel","type":"LAST","meanings":["A Welsh name derived from the Greek, signifying 'blooming luxuriantly, flourishing, rich.'. It is from Ithel that we have first the name Ap-Ithel, then by corruption, Bithell and Bethell."],"variants":[{"name":"Bithell","meanings":["Welsh: variant of   Bethel  ."]},{"name":"Bethell","meanings":["Welsh: variant of   Bethel  ."]}]},{"name":"Gwrgan","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Irish (Meath): shortened Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Geargáin</b> ‘descendant of <i>Geargán</i>’ or shortened from <b>Mac Geargáin</b> ‘son of <i>Geargán</i>’, a personal name from a diminutive of <i>garg</i> ‘fierce’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Gwrgan Ap Ithel was born about 0953, in Glamorgan, Wales. He married Ms. Fnu Verch Cynfyn about 0978, in Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom. He died in 1030, in Somme, Picardie, France, at the age of 78."},"et":{"Abt 953–1030":"umbes 0953–1030","0950–Female":"0950–Surnud","1024–Female":"1024–Surnud","0970–1079":"0970–1079","0953–1030":"0953–1030","0953":"0953","0950":"0950","0970":"0970","1079":"1079","1024":"1024","Abt 970":"umbes 0970","Abt 953":"umbes 0953","1030":"1030","Abt 978":"umbes 0978","Somme, Picardy, France":"Somme, Picardie, Prantsusmaa","Wales":"Wales, United Kingdom","of, , Morgannwg, Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales","of, , Glamorgan, Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom","Glamorgan, Glamorganshire, Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales"},"fi":{"Abt 953–1030":"noin 0953–1030","0950–Female":"